      <p>To evaluate the performance of Inpactor2 compared with other software, a similar methodology to the one proposed in [<xref rid="ref33" ref-type="bibr">33</xref>] was followed. First, Inpactor v.1.0 [<xref rid="ref34" ref-type="bibr">34</xref>], TEsorter v.1.3 [<xref rid="ref45" ref-type="bibr">45</xref>], Transposon Ultimate v.1.0 [<xref rid="ref28" ref-type="bibr">28</xref>], LTR_retriever v.2.9 [<xref rid="ref56" ref-type="bibr">56</xref>] and LTRharvest [<xref rid="ref57" ref-type="bibr">57</xref>] were selected for benchmarking given their methodologies for classifying LTR-RTs to the superfamily level. A workflow was established for each software, initially using LTR_FINDER v.1.0.7 as the LTR-RTs detector. Then, the <italic toggle="yes">O. sativa</italic> genome was annotated with RepeatMasker and performance metrics were extracted for each workflow. The metrics evaluated were: accuracy, precision, specificity, sensitivity, FDR and F1-score. Figure <xref rid="f1" ref-type="fig">1</xref> shows the schematic representation of the benchmarking metrics. In this study, TP, FN, TN and FP are the number of nucleotides belonging to each category (Figure <xref rid="f2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>).</p>
